  service_namespace  = "dynamodb"
  resource_id         = aws_appautoscaling_target.dynamodb_table_target.resource_id
  scalable_dimension = aws_appautoscaling_target.dynamodb_table_target.scalable_dimension

  step_scaling_policy {
    adjustment_type = "ChangeInCapacity"
    cooldown       = 60
    min_adjustment = 1

    metric_trigger {
      metric_name = "ConsumedReadCapacityUnits"
      namespace   = "AWS/DynamoDB"
      statistic  = "Sum"
      unit       = "Count"

      dimensions {
        name  = "Table"
        value = aws_dynamodb_table.dynamodb_table.name
      }

      abovelimit {
        perunit = 50. 
      }
    }
  }

  metric_aggregation_type          = "Average"
  policy_type                    = "StepScaling"
}
```

This configuration is for AWS DynamoDB with autoscaling policies using Terraform. A DynamoDB table is set up with a TTL attribute to allow expiration of data, reducing unnecessary data retention. Two App Autoscaling policies are configured to manage both read and write capacities separately, thereby optimizing the number of database calls and reducing costs.

