This configuration sets up an S3 bucket to store video content, a CloudFront distribution to distribute the content globally, and a Route53 CNAME record to point to the CloudFront distribution.

If additional SSL certificates and domain names are needed, AWS and ACM usage data should be adjusted.

Note: MMH checksum of the geo content might need adjustment, and GeoLocation’s restrictions can be widened for content availability across countries. And a public ACM certificate must be added to ensure HTTPS streaming.

