To enable Glacier access, you need to configure lifecycle policies separately in another Terraform block, specifically targeting Glacier storage for the action of transitioning objects to Glacier Storage. Here is a simple example of such a policy:

```hcl
resource "aws_s3_bucket_lifecycle_configuration" "bag_lifecycle" {
  bucket = aws_s3_bucket.glacier_bag.id

  rule {
    id     = "glacier_transition"
    enabled = true

    transition {
      days = 30
      storage_class = "GLACIER"
    }
  }
}
```

This configuration will enable objects to transition to Glacier after 30 days of storage in the bucket, which must be set up with versioning and server side encryption to qualify for Glacier storage transitions.

Note: Ensure the AWS provider support for "s3_glacier_transition" is available in your version of Terraform. How it interacts and configures with S3 storage classes may vary based on Terraform providers capabilities.

